"The Distributed Production Lab will analyze and respond to the challenges posed by new manufacturing technologies like 3-D printing that are already beginning to disrupt many facets of the traditional manufacturing system. In the near future, massive disruptions caused by distributed manufacturing will have global implications for everything from patents to raw material supply chains, and impact sectors as diverse as transportation, energy, and retail."
